1
00:00:20,353 --> 00:00:22,855
It's game over now.

2
00:00:24,942 --> 00:00:28,946
Yoo Jin, you have failed.

3
00:00:33,833 --> 00:00:35,868
Almighty Cha...

4
00:00:36,636 --> 00:00:40,040
I now denounce you
as the assistant conductor.

5
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:44,477
Please leave... From my orchestra!

6
00:00:44,477 --> 00:00:46,332
I don't want to.

7
00:00:47,047 --> 00:00:51,969
You said you'd give me
until tomorrow.

8
00:00:54,513 --> 00:00:56,243
Until tomorrow...

9
00:00:58,625 --> 00:01:00,593
This is my orchestra!

10
00:01:03,696 --> 00:01:05,536
"My orchestra"?

11
00:01:05,536 --> 00:01:07,192
Yes.

12
00:01:07,192 --> 00:01:09,202
This is my orchestra.

13
00:01:10,404 --> 00:01:13,699
Now that I think about it,
you do have until tomorrow.

14
00:01:13,699 --> 00:01:15,576
Go ahead then.

15
00:01:16,618 --> 00:01:18,887
I'll see you tomorrow.

16
00:01:43,353 --> 00:01:44,992
Let's try again.

17
00:01:44,992 --> 00:01:46,405
From the top...

18
00:01:49,568 --> 00:01:51,435
Our last rehearsal.

19
00:02:04,374 --> 00:02:11,321
Beethoven composed 'Eroica' for Napoleon.

20
00:02:11,321 --> 00:02:16,435
But Napoleon changed from

21
00:02:17,346 --> 00:02:19,330
a revolutionary to a tyrant.

22
00:02:19,330 --> 00:02:25,136
As soon as Beethoven heard it,
he changed the title to 'Eroica.'

23
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:29,723
He unknowingly decided to create

24
00:02:29,723 --> 00:02:34,360
his own revolution through music.

25
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:40,226
What's changed?

26
00:02:41,245 --> 00:02:44,122
The problem with the timpani
was too much excitement...

27
00:02:44,122 --> 00:02:46,657
but now, he's really down.

28
00:02:47,584 --> 00:02:50,069
Why does Clarinet have no energy?

29
00:02:53,106 --> 00:02:55,274
Viola is depressed.

30
00:02:57,510 --> 00:02:59,912
This is a depressing melody.

31
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:08,450
I get it now.

32
00:03:09,273 --> 00:03:11,976
I only cared about the sound

33
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:17,487
I ignored the feelings
that create the sound.

34
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:36,915
Timpani...

35
00:03:38,088 --> 00:03:40,052
It suits you better
when you're excited.

36
00:03:41,596 --> 00:03:43,015
Clarinet...

37
00:03:43,598 --> 00:03:45,737
You don't need to feel down.

38
00:03:45,737 --> 00:03:47,234
Viola...

39
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:50,647
Why are you so depressed?

40
00:03:56,904 --> 00:04:01,241
Tomorrow, will be our last session together.

41
00:04:07,831 --> 00:04:11,919
Sorry that we aren't good enough.

42
00:04:19,343 --> 00:04:20,954
It's not you.

43
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:23,804
The problem...

44
00:04:24,347 --> 00:04:25,849
Is me.

45
00:05:14,648 --> 00:05:19,486
I'd like both of you to take
charge of the orchestras.

46
00:05:19,486 --> 00:05:21,687
I don't teach losers.

47
00:05:22,573 --> 00:05:25,476
I'm in charge of
the leftovers anyway.

48
00:05:26,827 --> 00:05:29,162
I'm busy with the
concerto preparations.

49
00:05:30,372 --> 00:05:32,007
Do I have to?

50
00:05:34,585 --> 00:05:37,490
I heard you haven't found
students yet.

51
00:05:37,490 --> 00:05:39,825
But this is the board's decision.

52
00:05:41,925 --> 00:05:44,761
This will be the last chance
for one of the two orchestras.

53
00:05:44,761 --> 00:05:47,431
So please do your best.

54
00:05:48,314 --> 00:05:52,060
I guess we just can't keep both.

55
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:53,853
Off the record,

56
00:05:53,853 --> 00:05:56,689
I want the students to
enjoy the festival.

57
00:05:59,735 --> 00:06:01,870
Please, Professor Do.

58
00:06:05,449 --> 00:06:07,203
Alright.

59
00:06:11,709 --> 00:06:14,841
After they make us
compete with S Orchestra

60
00:06:14,841 --> 00:06:17,210
one of the orchestras will be disbanded?

61
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:19,571
Is that true?

62
00:06:19,571 --> 00:06:21,981
Mi Ran's uncle is a director
on our school board.

63
00:06:21,981 --> 00:06:24,259
It came from him.

64
00:06:24,259 --> 00:06:27,579
It doesn't make sense to have
two orchestras in one school.

65
00:06:27,579 --> 00:06:31,767
It's also annoying that they'd put us
on the same level as those losers.

66
00:06:31,767 --> 00:06:34,957
But they're in von Stresemann's
special orchestra.

67
00:06:35,479 --> 00:06:38,178
We'll begin our practice
two hours early starting today.

68
00:06:38,178 --> 00:06:40,379
We'll proceed even without a professor.

69
00:07:07,910 --> 00:07:09,729
Orabang! Let's go!

70
00:07:09,729 --> 00:07:11,497
One, two, three, four!

71
00:07:11,497 --> 00:07:14,934
Orabang's puppy is Nae Il's puppy.

72
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:17,916
Cheer up, cheer up, woof, woof, woof.

73
00:07:17,916 --> 00:07:19,584
Enough.

74
00:07:20,148 --> 00:07:23,643
When he gets mad, she gets scared
woof, woof, woof.

75
00:07:24,844 --> 00:07:27,012
She's our mascot alright.

76
00:07:28,681 --> 00:07:30,849
I'm sorry. Let's go again.

77
00:07:40,526 --> 00:07:42,491
Cha Yoo Jin.

78
00:07:43,085 --> 00:07:45,493
You're disqualified.

79
00:07:49,869 --> 00:07:53,272
He hasn't even started yet,
so why is he disqualified?

80
00:07:54,015 --> 00:07:59,916
Baby... he picked up
the baton that he dropped.

81
00:07:59,916 --> 00:08:02,715
What's wrong with picking up the baton?

82
00:08:02,715 --> 00:08:04,699
If it was a real performance

83
00:08:04,699 --> 00:08:08,267
because the conductor
lowered his body to pick up a baton

84
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:12,450
a major accident would have happened.

85
00:08:12,450 --> 00:08:14,870
This is not a real performance.

86
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:17,039
- Please?
- Stop.

87
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:20,083
I shouldn't have stopped the performance

88
00:08:20,083 --> 00:08:22,491
even if I had to
conduct with my hands.

89
00:08:22,961 --> 00:08:24,837
I apologize.

90
00:08:26,297 --> 00:08:29,927
Then you must accept the result.

91
00:08:32,471 --> 00:08:36,040
You will forfeit the title of
assistant conductor.

92
00:08:40,187 --> 00:08:42,856
Milch, I'll take revenge on you.

93
00:08:45,275 --> 00:08:49,238
If you really want to stay in the orchestra

94
00:08:49,238 --> 00:08:51,402
feel free to be my assistant.

95
00:08:52,074 --> 00:08:54,617
I think I'll have a lot of use for you.

96
00:08:54,617 --> 00:08:57,538
Since Baby comes along like a set.

97
00:08:57,538 --> 00:09:00,106
Orabang, don't be his assistant!

98
00:09:00,106 --> 00:09:02,331
What will you make him do?

99
00:09:02,331 --> 00:09:04,502
Too bad if you don't want to.

100
00:09:04,502 --> 00:09:06,058
Did I say I wouldn't?

101
00:09:06,058 --> 00:09:07,406
I'll do it.

102
00:09:07,965 --> 00:09:09,733
I'll do it!

103
00:09:13,839 --> 00:09:15,173
An assistant.

104
00:09:28,861 --> 00:09:30,462
Orabang!

105
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:37,176
Don't even get near me.
I'm allergic to fuzz.

106
00:09:37,176 --> 00:09:41,680
Don't worry. When I remove this,
I'll transform into Nae Il.

107
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:44,427
Don't you know I'm more
allergic to Nae Il?

108
00:09:59,999 --> 00:10:02,034
Then just this...

109
00:10:02,034 --> 00:10:04,236
I'll hold just this.

110
00:10:13,988 --> 00:10:18,368
But still, your conducting
is the best.

111
00:10:21,622 --> 00:10:22,955
- Hey!
- But I'm Nae Il now.

112
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:25,124
I'm really allergic to fuzz.

113
00:10:40,474 --> 00:10:43,821
[Lesson 4]

114
00:10:51,984 --> 00:10:54,694
It's just me,
why are you trying so hard?

115
00:10:54,694 --> 00:10:58,016
Don't worry about anything.
Pay more attention to Yoo Jin.

116
00:10:58,016 --> 00:10:59,776
You know this is a bribe right?

117
00:10:59,776 --> 00:11:02,447
I always focus on my students.

118
00:11:02,447 --> 00:11:06,092
Then why'd you let that
crook mess with my son?

119
00:11:06,092 --> 00:11:07,167
What are you talking about?

120
00:11:07,167 --> 00:11:09,675
I heard from more than 20 students,

121
00:11:09,675 --> 00:11:11,463
he had my son run around
and hand out sandwiches.

122
00:11:11,463 --> 00:11:13,060
Is that so?

123
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:15,518
Seriously? You didn't know?

124
00:11:18,810 --> 00:11:21,656
Yoo Jin is doing great.

125
00:11:21,656 --> 00:11:22,807
He's made many friends,

126
00:11:22,807 --> 00:11:25,644
performed duets
with a violinist and pianist.

127
00:11:25,644 --> 00:11:27,359
We couldn't imagine that before.

128
00:11:27,359 --> 00:11:30,858
I heard about the violin,
but he played a piano duet?

129
00:11:30,858 --> 00:11:32,353
Professor Ahn...

130
00:11:35,461 --> 00:11:40,098
You... keep proceeding
to be a mom with a trap.

131
00:11:41,767 --> 00:11:45,637
I won't give you anymore intel.
Give up.

132
00:11:46,789 --> 00:11:51,057
Stop putting it on.
Your skin is illuminating already.

133
00:11:51,057 --> 00:11:53,672
Hey, thank you.

134
00:11:53,672 --> 00:11:55,132
You should try
the translucent makeup, too.

135
00:11:55,132 --> 00:11:57,217
I'm single, so I should look
different from a married woman.

136
00:11:57,217 --> 00:11:59,070
Bye.

137
00:12:00,219 --> 00:12:02,415
Don't eat too much.
You'll gain weight.

138
00:12:03,973 --> 00:12:06,228
Piano duet?

139
00:12:06,727 --> 00:12:10,096
It'll be no problem to find
whom he played with.

140
00:12:13,317 --> 00:12:20,691
I haven't met a pianist who
understands Messiaen more than you.

141
00:12:22,326 --> 00:12:24,641
Although you've stopped
playing the piano,

142
00:12:25,871 --> 00:12:33,088
your heart is the same..

143
00:12:40,051 --> 00:12:41,856
Mina...

144
00:12:41,856 --> 00:12:43,105
Yes?

145
00:12:46,724 --> 00:12:48,476
Professor...

146
00:12:48,476 --> 00:12:51,355
It's time for
our S Orchestra's lesson.

147
00:12:53,564 --> 00:12:57,444
How did you know
where to find me?

148
00:12:58,653 --> 00:13:03,596
I reserved the palace tickets
for you as your assistant.

149
00:13:03,596 --> 00:13:05,957
I came to pick you up
as your assistant.

150
00:13:06,719 --> 00:13:08,258
You had a lesson?

151
00:13:08,258 --> 00:13:10,122
I didn't know...

152
00:13:12,084 --> 00:13:16,395
No, self-study is part of education.

153
00:13:16,395 --> 00:13:21,112
The members are determined to have
a lesson today, they're waiting for you.

154
00:13:21,112 --> 00:13:23,781
The students are waiting for
you, so you should go.

155
00:13:24,369 --> 00:13:26,223
I'm sorry that I wasted your time.

156
00:13:26,223 --> 00:13:30,932
Mina! I have time,
you may have all of it!

157
00:13:41,071 --> 00:13:44,474
Professor, it's almost time for our lesson.

158
00:13:45,409 --> 00:13:48,412
Go ahead first.
I'll follow you.

159
00:13:48,412 --> 00:13:51,282
Then I'll wait for you
in the lobby.

160
00:14:05,144 --> 00:14:07,279
Why isn't he coming...

161
00:14:09,349 --> 00:14:11,417
We have a lot to do...

162
00:14:15,207 --> 00:14:16,481
Yoo Jin!

163
00:14:16,481 --> 00:14:18,415
What's this?

164
00:14:19,276 --> 00:14:21,653
What about the Professor?
Isn't he here yet?

165
00:14:21,653 --> 00:14:22,661
You don't know as his assistant?

166
00:14:22,661 --> 00:14:25,764
When is he going to give us a lesson?
Aren't we getting a lesson?

167
00:14:25,764 --> 00:14:28,433
Almighty Cha!

168
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:34,441
Can't you come just for
a bit, Almighty Cha?

169
00:14:34,441 --> 00:14:36,418
We can't practice like this.

170
00:14:36,418 --> 00:14:38,377
- What?
- That's right, my best friend!

171
00:14:38,377 --> 00:14:41,423
You've upgraded them so
far, do some more!

172
00:14:41,423 --> 00:14:42,781
Please.

173
00:14:42,781 --> 00:14:47,386
- Yes, please.
- Just once.

174
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:53,977
The dynamic shouldn't grow
between the 15th and 21st.

175
00:14:53,977 --> 00:14:55,395
Continue with the piano.

176
00:14:55,395 --> 00:14:58,651
I thought a crescendo
would be fitting.

177
00:14:59,233 --> 00:15:02,501
See? It's better to
listen to Orabang, right?

178
00:15:02,501 --> 00:15:05,471
Raise your hand if you
have any questions.

179
00:15:05,471 --> 00:15:07,289
- Me, Timpani!
- Now now now...

180
00:15:07,289 --> 00:15:08,908
It'll be faster to practice.

181
00:15:08,908 --> 00:15:11,310
- Yoo Jin, why don't you conduct?
- What?

182
00:15:11,310 --> 00:15:13,270
Just do it.

183
00:15:13,270 --> 00:15:15,127
- Orabang, do it.
- Sit down everyone.

184
00:15:15,127 --> 00:15:16,861
Hey...

185
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:19,947
Have fun with your practice!

186
00:15:24,091 --> 00:15:26,677
Remember allegro in the first movement.

187
00:15:26,677 --> 00:15:28,553
Lively and cheerful.

188
00:15:28,553 --> 00:15:34,226
Isn't that where the conductor stands, Assistant?

189
00:15:39,398 --> 00:15:43,943
What are you doing by letting
the assistant stand on my podium?

190
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:46,363
- I'm sorry, I was...
- Assistant...

191
00:15:46,363 --> 00:15:49,666
Keep your mouth shut.
I'm the one talking.

192
00:15:51,368 --> 00:15:55,246
It's all because of you, Milch.
Why do you keep blaming Orabang?

193
00:15:56,540 --> 00:15:59,718
Relax! Relax, Baby.

194
00:16:00,335 --> 00:16:03,070
Assistant, you're fired now.

195
00:16:06,465 --> 00:16:09,601
Assistant Conductor, then Assistant...

196
00:16:09,601 --> 00:16:11,995
You keep giving it to
him and taking it back.

197
00:16:11,995 --> 00:16:14,197
You're bad, Milch!

198
00:16:15,407 --> 00:16:17,142
That's true.

199
00:16:17,728 --> 00:16:24,450
Then Yoo Jin, be the conductor
instead of the professor.

200
00:16:25,861 --> 00:16:35,285
Then from this moment, I'll withdraw
from von Stresemann's S Orchestra.

201
00:16:38,401 --> 00:16:41,209
Don't worry about me...

202
00:16:41,209 --> 00:16:44,922
and practice with that new conductor.

203
00:16:46,632 --> 00:16:49,568
I wish you the best of luck.

204
00:16:50,844 --> 00:16:51,887
Professor...

205
00:16:51,887 --> 00:16:54,701
Milch! Milch!

206
00:16:58,602 --> 00:17:00,874
What's this? Why are you
packing up your instruments?

207
00:17:00,874 --> 00:17:02,994
We're von Stresemann's orchestra.

208
00:17:02,994 --> 00:17:05,734
If he quits, what's the point.

209
00:17:05,734 --> 00:17:09,363
We're the Special orchestra!
Don't pretend this is new.

210
00:17:09,363 --> 00:17:11,894
Have we ever been members
of an orchestra?

211
00:17:12,765 --> 00:17:15,480
Except for Su Min...

212
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:18,601
It's the first time for all of us...
being part of an orchestra.

213
00:17:19,956 --> 00:17:22,587
That's why we are
going to do our best!

214
00:17:22,587 --> 00:17:24,822
Where else can we play if not here?

215
00:17:28,382 --> 00:17:31,690
Don't worry.
We have Orabang with us!

216
00:17:31,690 --> 00:17:35,020
We can do anything
as long as we have Orabang!

217
00:17:35,020 --> 00:17:37,722
Don't worry everybody!
We have Orabang!

218
00:17:39,017 --> 00:17:41,144
As long as we have Almighty Cha,
there is no problem!

219
00:17:41,144 --> 00:17:43,229
Wait. I never said I'd do it.

220
00:17:43,229 --> 00:17:45,424
Yoo Jin who gives us lessons is better

221
00:17:45,424 --> 00:17:47,150
than the professor who doesn't teach us.

222
00:17:47,150 --> 00:17:50,387
His personality is not great,
but his conducting is good.

223
00:17:50,387 --> 00:17:52,671
Well, at least it's Yoo Jin.

224
00:17:52,671 --> 00:17:55,701
Our new conductor, Cha Yoo Jin!

225
00:17:55,701 --> 00:18:06,111
Cha Yoo Jin! Cha Yoo Jin!

226
00:18:07,963 --> 00:18:09,723
Everyone knows Seung Oh, right?

227
00:18:09,723 --> 00:18:12,992
We can't just sit around
waiting for Stresemann.

228
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:18,588
As your head professor I've made
up my mind. How bad could it be?

229
00:18:18,588 --> 00:18:21,225
This is the decision I made
as the professor in charge.

230
00:18:21,225 --> 00:18:25,211
Of course a conducting major is
better than a piano major.

231
00:18:25,211 --> 00:18:26,978
I understand.

232
00:18:29,875 --> 00:18:32,810
Turn off your cellphones
during practice!

233
00:18:34,370 --> 00:18:38,034
Professor Franz withdrew
from S Orchestra!

234
00:18:38,034 --> 00:18:39,184
What happened?

235
00:18:39,184 --> 00:18:43,775
Yoo Jin got caught for
conducting during practice...

236
00:18:43,775 --> 00:18:45,791
So the professor withdrew.

237
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:48,259
Yoo Jin became the conductor...

238
00:18:51,673 --> 00:18:53,700
My my...

239
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:57,804
Even this class has
found a new conductor.

240
00:19:10,483 --> 00:19:13,654
Congratulations on becoming
the conductor, Orabang!

241
00:19:16,657 --> 00:19:19,451
Congratulations, congratulations...

242
00:19:19,451 --> 00:19:21,853
Do you think this situation
deserves 'congratulations'?

243
00:19:23,956 --> 00:19:27,625
You should be happy as
long as you can conduct.

244
00:19:27,625 --> 00:19:31,255
You wanted to conduct, right?

245
00:19:32,104 --> 00:19:34,650
I don't know what he's up to.

246
00:19:37,189 --> 00:19:38,774
Loud!

247
00:19:49,021 --> 00:19:54,679
I have an important announcement
to make regarding

248
00:19:55,588 --> 00:19:58,430
our Orchestra Autumn Concert.

249
00:20:00,939 --> 00:20:04,723
Between our university's
Han Eum orchestra..

250
00:20:05,579 --> 00:20:08,250
It's too complicated..

251
00:20:08,250 --> 00:20:14,506
From now on it's A Orchestra,
and Special Orchestra is S.

252
00:20:14,506 --> 00:20:19,944
A Orchestra will participate in
the regular fall performance

253
00:20:20,819 --> 00:20:25,222
and the S Orchestra will also perform.

254
00:20:28,460 --> 00:20:32,564
The performance is a
battle between A and S!

255
00:20:33,108 --> 00:20:36,301
The team that loses

256
00:20:36,301 --> 00:20:37,613
will be disbanded.

257
00:20:37,613 --> 00:20:39,546
Disbanded?

258
00:20:39,546 --> 00:20:42,373
What do you mean, 'disbanded'? Gone...

259
00:20:51,709 --> 00:20:56,256
Good luck, A and S!

260
00:20:56,922 --> 00:21:00,492
Do your best!

261
00:21:05,349 --> 00:21:08,166
I knew Milch was strange.

262
00:21:08,166 --> 00:21:11,778
- Milch is super eccentric.
- Is he really a genius?

263
00:21:11,778 --> 00:21:14,239
Genius? He's just an old crook!

264
00:21:14,239 --> 00:21:15,692
I was uneasy that he
made me a conductor,

265
00:21:15,692 --> 00:21:17,960
whether it was out
of spite or not...

266
00:21:19,077 --> 00:21:20,800
Was this it?

267
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:23,169
You'll put us in a match
and disband us?

268
00:21:25,083 --> 00:21:26,351
Nae Il.

269
00:21:26,351 --> 00:21:28,353
Yes, Orabang.

270
00:21:28,914 --> 00:21:30,849
Let's do this.

271
00:21:31,999 --> 00:21:34,920
You think you can
disband my orchestra?

272
00:21:35,753 --> 00:21:38,590
Orabang, you're so cool.

273
00:21:39,217 --> 00:21:40,818
Yoo Jin!

274
00:21:42,510 --> 00:21:44,470
You heard the announcement, right?

275
00:21:44,470 --> 00:21:45,513
Yes.

276
00:21:45,513 --> 00:21:49,424
Who's going to conduct the
S Orchestra now that this happened?

277
00:21:49,977 --> 00:21:51,290
I will.

278
00:21:54,064 --> 00:21:58,443
I'm the conductor of S Orchestra.

279
00:21:58,443 --> 00:22:01,777
Let's practice. I think practice
is the only way to survive.

280
00:22:01,777 --> 00:22:04,855
Can we? Can we really beat A Orchestra?

281
00:22:04,855 --> 00:22:06,404
Of course.

282
00:22:07,592 --> 00:22:10,545
They are... really good.

283
00:22:10,545 --> 00:22:12,498
All of them have studied abroad.

284
00:22:12,498 --> 00:22:15,334
Taking A's side right now?
Overseas so what?

285
00:22:15,334 --> 00:22:17,087
Money takes care of that.

286
00:22:17,087 --> 00:22:18,970
Their leader, bandmaster,

287
00:22:18,970 --> 00:22:22,607
will be going to Vienna.

288
00:22:25,410 --> 00:22:26,945
What are you doing?

289
00:22:26,945 --> 00:22:28,746
Aren't you going to practice?

290
00:22:29,348 --> 00:22:31,518
Hurry up!

291
00:22:31,518 --> 00:22:33,553
The losing team will be disbanded!

292
00:22:34,479 --> 00:22:36,049
We lack in skills and experience,

293
00:22:36,049 --> 00:22:38,317
so we have to catch
up with practice.

294
00:22:38,317 --> 00:22:40,068
We have three weeks
until the concert.

295
00:22:40,068 --> 00:22:42,774
We have to master up to the
fourth movement by then.

296
00:22:42,774 --> 00:22:45,042
We don't have enough time or skill.

297
00:22:45,811 --> 00:22:49,781
On top of that, if we lose,
the orchestra will get disbanded.

298
00:22:51,829 --> 00:22:53,738
We'll double our practice from today.

299
00:22:53,738 --> 00:22:56,666
If you fall behind, get more
individual lessons to catch up.

300
00:22:56,666 --> 00:22:58,301
Understood?

301
00:22:59,778 --> 00:23:01,613
Tuning, Oboe!

302
00:23:06,151 --> 00:23:08,347
- Watch my instrument!
- Sorry.

303
00:23:08,347 --> 00:23:10,014
I'm sorry.

304
00:23:10,014 --> 00:23:12,643
No one is allowed to be late
from now.

305
00:23:23,904 --> 00:23:29,008
How lucky. I wish there was room for a piano.

306
00:23:49,179 --> 00:23:51,805
Don't even bring up Professor Ahn.

307
00:23:51,805 --> 00:23:54,859
He recommended the Fart Song.

308
00:23:54,859 --> 00:23:57,094
Fart Song! Fart Song!

309
00:23:58,228 --> 00:23:59,438
Yes.

310
00:23:59,438 --> 00:24:01,565
Tell me if you see any talent.

311
00:24:01,565 --> 00:24:04,653
I'll test them
and make a decision.

312
00:24:13,218 --> 00:24:16,721
What a complete mess...

313
00:24:17,499 --> 00:24:20,001
This is why we fall behind Sae Yeon.

314
00:24:39,895 --> 00:24:41,980
This isn't wrong.

315
00:24:41,980 --> 00:24:44,443
This is different.

316
00:24:44,443 --> 00:24:46,805
Something is different.

317
00:24:46,805 --> 00:24:50,241
It has power of attracting
people's ears and hearts.

318
00:24:57,206 --> 00:25:00,675
If I trim it and teach it,
how much could it grow?

319
00:25:01,946 --> 00:25:04,081
How much could it change?

320
00:25:19,951 --> 00:25:21,886
I'm late for class!

321
00:25:23,188 --> 00:25:25,558
My goodness...

322
00:25:26,358 --> 00:25:29,027
We'll move up our practice
by one hour tomorrow.

323
00:25:34,099 --> 00:25:36,134
Should we move it up by two hours?

324
00:25:42,374 --> 00:25:45,020
Hey hey! Guys!

325
00:25:45,020 --> 00:25:47,936
Let's move it up by an hour
tomorrow like Yoo Jin said

326
00:25:47,936 --> 00:25:49,514
and change the schedule after that.

327
00:25:49,514 --> 00:25:51,925
Everyone's hungry, right?
We should eat...

328
00:25:51,925 --> 00:25:55,472
Yes! My father will treat you to dinner!

329
00:25:56,388 --> 00:25:59,518
Here's the food!

330
00:25:59,518 --> 00:26:00,978
It looks great.

331
00:26:00,978 --> 00:26:03,355
Here, enjoy.

332
00:26:03,355 --> 00:26:05,617
Thank you.

333
00:26:06,531 --> 00:26:09,200
- Wait just a bit. I'll bring it out soon.
- Yes!

334
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:10,669
Thanks, Father!

335
00:26:10,669 --> 00:26:15,173
I finally understand why Professor
appointed you as the concertmaster.

336
00:26:15,173 --> 00:26:18,911
Of course! I'll manage well in
the middle, so just trust me.

337
00:26:18,911 --> 00:26:20,329
Okay.

338
00:26:20,329 --> 00:26:24,334
By the way, aren't we
working hard for nothing?

339
00:26:24,334 --> 00:26:27,372
How could we defeat A Orchestra?

340
00:26:27,372 --> 00:26:29,888
They're no big deal.

341
00:26:29,888 --> 00:26:35,426
They're just nerds with boring
music and thoughts after all.

342
00:26:37,389 --> 00:26:43,121
We need losers like this to
show us how good we are.

343
00:26:43,121 --> 00:26:47,858
They show us how low the floor is.

344
00:26:48,482 --> 00:26:51,193
- What?
- No need to deal with them.

345
00:26:51,193 --> 00:26:54,239
You started first. Let's stop.

346
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:57,773
Shi Won, why are you doing this?

347
00:26:57,773 --> 00:26:59,064
What a stuck-up.

348
00:26:59,064 --> 00:27:01,566
Our Shi Won is truly superior.

349
00:27:02,079 --> 00:27:05,684
Different from a loser like you.

350
00:27:05,684 --> 00:27:07,876
What do you mean loser?

351
00:27:07,876 --> 00:27:10,963
Our bandmaster is extremely talented!

352
00:27:10,963 --> 00:27:15,433
Yeah! You want to a battle
between bandmasters?

353
00:27:15,433 --> 00:27:16,637
Sure!

354
00:27:18,370 --> 00:27:19,771
Sounds interesting.

355
00:27:19,771 --> 00:27:22,724
- Battle?
- Stop, Jay Young.

356
00:27:22,724 --> 00:27:25,951
Just apologize and end it here.

357
00:27:25,951 --> 00:27:27,062
She's right.

358
00:27:27,062 --> 00:27:29,089
What, why? You think I'll lose?

359
00:27:29,089 --> 00:27:31,249
Why don't we have a battle?

360
00:27:32,945 --> 00:27:35,221
If you're afraid,
you can drop out.

361
00:27:43,912 --> 00:27:46,432
Czardas, okay?

362
00:27:47,465 --> 00:27:48,958
Okay.

363
00:27:48,958 --> 00:27:51,296
Let's go, S Orchestra!

364
00:27:51,296 --> 00:27:54,445
Yoo Il Lak! Yoo Il Lak!

365
00:27:56,775 --> 00:27:59,911
Il Lak, it's better to stop now.

366
00:27:59,911 --> 00:28:01,579
Go away, you're not helpful!

367
00:28:01,579 --> 00:28:03,350
I'm not the old Yoo Il Lak!

368
00:28:03,350 --> 00:28:05,485
This is not like you.

369
00:28:06,351 --> 00:28:08,689
I think I have to show them,

370
00:28:08,689 --> 00:28:10,576
the difference between us!

371
00:28:26,937 --> 00:28:30,208
Czardas... Gypsy's Dance.

372
00:28:30,208 --> 00:28:33,338
Like gypsies who are free but sorrowful...

373
00:28:34,423 --> 00:28:38,527
Yes, you're doing well, my son.

374
00:29:08,540 --> 00:29:13,026
Cheer up, Il Lak!
Run so that no one can catch up!

375
00:29:32,231 --> 00:29:36,318
Don't fall down.
Just like that... just like that...

376
00:29:36,318 --> 00:29:38,520
Just a little more...

377
00:29:44,849 --> 00:29:46,727
Bummer.

378
00:30:05,122 --> 00:30:06,682
You were almost there!

379
00:30:06,682 --> 00:30:10,308
If only you didn't make a mistake, right?

380
00:30:10,308 --> 00:30:13,353
If your fingers didn't slip,
you'd have won.

381
00:30:13,353 --> 00:30:16,108
Is it a mistake when a
violinist's fingers slip?

382
00:30:16,701 --> 00:30:18,576
It's also his level.

383
00:30:20,112 --> 00:30:23,761
Shi Won will be going to Vienna,

384
00:30:23,761 --> 00:30:25,729
you have nothing to
be embarrassed about.

385
00:30:26,224 --> 00:30:27,859
Let's go now.

386
00:30:45,076 --> 00:30:47,107
Good job!

387
00:30:47,107 --> 00:30:48,946
Good job, my son.

388
00:30:51,616 --> 00:30:55,188
Is it because I was cutting onions?
Why are my eyes hurting?

389
00:30:57,355 --> 00:30:59,524
You used everything to fight him.

390
00:30:59,524 --> 00:31:01,445
I thought I had to.

391
00:31:01,445 --> 00:31:04,948
He's pretty good for someone
who plays the electric violin.

392
00:31:12,539 --> 00:31:14,607
Your card has insufficient funds..

393
00:31:15,473 --> 00:31:17,904
Insufficient.. Funds..?

394
00:31:24,676 --> 00:31:26,446
Mini Min Hee?

395
00:31:27,886 --> 00:31:29,515
Hello?

396
00:31:30,307 --> 00:31:34,592
Wait for Nae Il's giant food storage!

397
00:31:38,857 --> 00:31:41,083
I'm sorry.

398
00:31:41,083 --> 00:31:44,902
My money comes in within 2 days..

399
00:31:46,838 --> 00:31:51,041
It's okay. Thank you for thinking of me.

400
00:31:51,952 --> 00:31:54,039
Tada! I have almonds here.

401
00:31:54,039 --> 00:31:57,568
My mom sent it to me to snack on.

402
00:31:57,568 --> 00:31:59,803
Here.

403
00:32:01,651 --> 00:32:03,046
What?

404
00:32:03,046 --> 00:32:05,008
Let's share this.

405
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:08,559
No, I want you to have it. I'm fine.

406
00:32:08,559 --> 00:32:10,194
Thank you.

407
00:32:16,701 --> 00:32:18,769
Hey.. What's wrong?

408
00:32:19,314 --> 00:32:20,772
I smell food..

409
00:32:20,772 --> 00:32:22,734
You smell food?

410
00:32:23,819 --> 00:32:25,821
Steak..

411
00:32:25,821 --> 00:32:27,222
Soup!

412
00:32:30,075 --> 00:32:32,286
And bread!

413
00:32:32,286 --> 00:32:33,787
Mini Min Hee!

414
00:32:40,058 --> 00:32:43,341
I'm sorry. That was rude!

415
00:32:43,341 --> 00:32:47,426
I don't know
why I lose my mind over food.

416
00:32:47,426 --> 00:32:51,262
I think it's normal. Food
is the most important.

417
00:32:51,972 --> 00:32:54,040
It is not normal!

418
00:32:56,602 --> 00:32:59,271
- Eat.
- Thank you.

419
00:32:59,897 --> 00:33:02,065
Enjoy, mini Min Hee.

420
00:33:06,337 --> 00:33:08,614
It's delicious.

421
00:33:08,614 --> 00:33:12,199
Do you get to eat
like this everyday?

422
00:33:12,199 --> 00:33:14,776
Of course, every single day!

423
00:33:21,919 --> 00:33:25,756
Is this instant? Orabang, your
efforts are a bit insufficient.

424
00:33:25,756 --> 00:33:28,008
You're complaining about free food?

425
00:33:28,008 --> 00:33:29,507
If you're going to be picky, leave.

426
00:33:29,507 --> 00:33:32,697
It's instant soup
but I can still feel the love.

427
00:33:32,697 --> 00:33:34,665
Mini Min Hee!

428
00:33:35,849 --> 00:33:38,058
Nothing like that is in there.

429
00:33:38,058 --> 00:33:39,768
Just eat then leave.

430
00:33:39,768 --> 00:33:42,312
You realize your contrabass
is off melody right?

431
00:33:42,312 --> 00:33:45,598
Your bowing is wrong because
you don't show up for practice.

432
00:33:46,151 --> 00:33:48,846
I'm sorry. I have a part-time job...

433
00:33:48,846 --> 00:33:52,689
Right, she's late because she has a job.

434
00:33:52,689 --> 00:33:54,407
You can quit your part-time job.

435
00:33:54,407 --> 00:33:56,264
Then...

436
00:33:56,264 --> 00:33:58,377
I can't pay my school fees...

437
00:33:58,377 --> 00:33:59,997
Then quit coming to school.

438
00:33:59,997 --> 00:34:01,792
If you can't come to practice
because of school fees

439
00:34:01,792 --> 00:34:04,336
there is no point of school.

440
00:34:04,336 --> 00:34:06,044
Why is there no point?

441
00:34:06,044 --> 00:34:08,631
Fantasy of campus!
Campus couple!

442
00:34:08,631 --> 00:34:10,924
We met on campus too, Orabang!

443
00:34:10,924 --> 00:34:12,536
Self-study would be better.

444
00:34:12,536 --> 00:34:17,566
No one recognizes performers
who don't go to college.

445
00:34:17,566 --> 00:34:22,139
Is it a solution or
sympathy that you want?

446
00:34:30,571 --> 00:34:32,114
Thank you for food.

447
00:34:32,114 --> 00:34:34,372
Mini Min Hee, what's wrong?

448
00:34:34,372 --> 00:34:36,686
Have some more..

449
00:34:40,372 --> 00:34:44,970
Mini Min Hee! Don't leave!

450
00:34:54,136 --> 00:34:56,471
They drank it clean.

451
00:34:56,471 --> 00:34:58,758
Just leave me.

452
00:35:07,149 --> 00:35:08,884
Mini Min Hee!

453
00:35:11,153 --> 00:35:14,979
Tada! I looked everywhere
in my place and found it!

454
00:35:14,979 --> 00:35:16,742
Should we have some
rice cakes after we're done here?

455
00:35:16,742 --> 00:35:19,644
Which one do you want to eat?
I like tuna with mayonnaise.

456
00:35:20,511 --> 00:35:23,079
I'm going to quit the orchestra.

457
00:35:23,079 --> 00:35:25,375
What? Why?

458
00:35:25,375 --> 00:35:27,262
Sunbae was right.

459
00:35:27,262 --> 00:35:29,490
I was only looking for an excuse.

460
00:35:29,490 --> 00:35:31,882
No, it's not an excuse.

461
00:35:31,882 --> 00:35:34,578
If you quit your part-time job, you
have to quit the orchestra, too.

462
00:35:34,578 --> 00:35:36,935
That's why you did it, right?

463
00:35:39,139 --> 00:35:41,107
Orabang was mean.

464
00:35:45,145 --> 00:35:47,647
He doesn't deserve to call me!

465
00:35:49,021 --> 00:35:51,902
Orabang, it's no use to call
me even if you missed me!

466
00:35:51,902 --> 00:35:54,238
Because we'll be separated for a while!

467
00:35:57,991 --> 00:35:59,339
What?

468
00:35:59,816 --> 00:36:01,388
Conductor's score?

469
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:04,435
Where did I leave it?

470
00:36:04,996 --> 00:36:07,918
Dress room... In the dress room!

471
00:36:08,488 --> 00:36:10,168
Why did I go there?

472
00:36:10,168 --> 00:36:12,320
I'm not sure.

473
00:36:15,133 --> 00:36:19,137
Mini Min Hee, I'm sorry.
I have to go now.

474
00:36:21,682 --> 00:36:24,417
Why? Do you need my help?

475
00:36:28,564 --> 00:36:30,132
This?

476
00:36:43,287 --> 00:36:45,055
Goodbye.

477
00:36:56,457 --> 00:36:57,549
Your friend?

478
00:36:57,549 --> 00:36:59,317
Yes, she's my friend.

479
00:36:59,317 --> 00:37:01,490
They must be a married couple.

480
00:37:03,304 --> 00:37:06,685
A little new bride... how cute.

481
00:37:06,685 --> 00:37:08,974
Can't you hurry up?
You took my...

482
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:13,596
Hey, hey hey! Il Lak!

483
00:37:14,651 --> 00:37:16,919
- Your place is nice.
- Are you drunk?

484
00:37:17,863 --> 00:37:19,270
What're you doing?

485
00:37:19,270 --> 00:37:21,116
My apologies.

486
00:37:21,116 --> 00:37:23,160
I really tried to stop him...

487
00:37:23,160 --> 00:37:26,958
But Il Lak kept insisting on
coming to Almighty Cha's place...

488
00:37:26,958 --> 00:37:28,498
Almighty Cha?

489
00:37:28,498 --> 00:37:31,000
Is that what you call me, Timpani?

490
00:37:31,585 --> 00:37:35,464
Almighty Cha, you... remember me?

491
00:37:35,464 --> 00:37:38,035
You're my member, so of course I remember you.

492
00:37:38,035 --> 00:37:40,924
You're the only one
who plays adequately.

493
00:37:44,139 --> 00:37:47,935
The highest grade steak.
Do you want to eat it now?

494
00:37:47,935 --> 00:37:50,137
I had a steak for dinner.

495
00:37:51,081 --> 00:37:52,532
Really?

496
00:37:52,532 --> 00:37:54,091
Then...

497
00:37:54,091 --> 00:37:56,594
Eat it tomorrow.

498
00:37:56,594 --> 00:37:59,856
You shouldn't store meat there.
Move aside!

499
00:37:59,856 --> 00:38:02,758
You have to keep it in here.

500
00:38:08,539 --> 00:38:12,417
Nae Il, you know how
to use my refrigerator?

501
00:38:12,417 --> 00:38:14,002
How did you get in here?

502
00:38:14,002 --> 00:38:16,088
Well, the door was open.

503
00:38:16,088 --> 00:38:18,966
Orabang, I'll go find
your conductor's score.

504
00:38:18,966 --> 00:38:21,510
Hey! Nae Il, why
did you come here?

505
00:38:21,510 --> 00:38:25,247
Stalker! Now you barge
into someone's home?

506
00:38:27,516 --> 00:38:29,384
Everyone shut up!

507
00:38:35,065 --> 00:38:39,068
Orabang, I'll keep quiet
and find the score.

508
00:38:42,787 --> 00:38:44,239
Yoo Il Lak.

509
00:38:44,739 --> 00:38:46,577
Why did you bring me steak?

510
00:38:47,119 --> 00:38:49,156
It's my lesson fee.

511
00:38:52,165 --> 00:38:53,458
My best friend!

512
00:38:53,458 --> 00:38:55,750
I mean, mentor.

513
00:38:55,750 --> 00:38:57,913
Give me private lessons.

514
00:38:57,913 --> 00:39:00,672
You're the only one
I can trust now.

515
00:39:00,672 --> 00:39:03,307
You're better than Shi Won Jung.

516
00:39:03,307 --> 00:39:04,875
Right?

517
00:39:28,599 --> 00:39:30,996
What's the use of cutting them nicely?
Taste is what's important.

518
00:39:30,996 --> 00:39:32,539
How ignorant.

519
00:39:32,539 --> 00:39:34,208
You have to cut them diagonally

520
00:39:34,208 --> 00:39:37,252
so that they have a wider surface
to give more flavor.

521
00:39:37,252 --> 00:39:39,463
I know Orabang's preference better.

522
00:39:39,463 --> 00:39:41,462
He won't eat that hodgepodge stew!

523
00:39:41,462 --> 00:39:43,214
What? Hodgepodge?

524
00:39:43,214 --> 00:39:45,761
Once Almighty Cha tastes my spicy
sausage stew with the golden ratio

525
00:39:45,761 --> 00:39:50,198
he'll get tired of your bland cooking.

526
00:39:51,016 --> 00:39:53,051
Bland?

527
00:39:53,644 --> 00:39:56,381
- Is That all you have to say?
- Yes.

528
00:39:57,027 --> 00:39:59,233
I'll show you. I'm good at cutting too.

529
00:39:59,233 --> 00:40:00,646
What the heck are you doing?

530
00:40:00,646 --> 00:40:03,140
Get away from my Orabang, please!

531
00:40:03,140 --> 00:40:05,141
You get away from him!

532
00:40:05,763 --> 00:40:07,231
Drink water.

533
00:40:08,325 --> 00:40:10,202
No, I don't want it!

534
00:40:10,202 --> 00:40:11,937
If you're not here for
a lesson, leave.

535
00:40:12,577 --> 00:40:14,512
Do you hate me, too?

536
00:40:14,512 --> 00:40:16,814
You don't want me as
your bandmaster or friend?

537
00:40:16,814 --> 00:40:18,574
What are you talking about?

538
00:40:18,574 --> 00:40:21,899
I don't need any lessons.

539
00:40:21,899 --> 00:40:26,203
What's the use of getting lessons?
I won't make it anyway.

540
00:40:27,057 --> 00:40:29,132
No, you...

541
00:40:31,562 --> 00:40:33,497
You are...

542
00:40:33,497 --> 00:40:35,642
You're not a bad bandmaster.

543
00:40:35,642 --> 00:40:36,854
Really?

544
00:40:36,854 --> 00:40:40,524
How how... How am I not
a bad bandmaster?

545
00:40:41,483 --> 00:40:43,193
The smell...

546
00:40:43,193 --> 00:40:45,865
You are...

547
00:40:45,865 --> 00:40:49,060
You make the members feel
comfortable.

548
00:40:49,060 --> 00:40:51,869
- And?
- Do I have to do more?

549
00:40:51,869 --> 00:40:54,580
- More, more.
- You are...

550
00:40:54,580 --> 00:40:58,134
Right, you have an
outgoing personality.

551
00:41:02,004 --> 00:41:04,798
So I don't have skills after all.

552
00:41:04,798 --> 00:41:06,892
I want to do well, too.

553
00:41:06,892 --> 00:41:09,759
But these fingers don't listen to me.

554
00:41:09,759 --> 00:41:13,679
I am... not even qualified!

555
00:41:13,679 --> 00:41:15,105
Then quit being the bandmaster.

556
00:41:15,105 --> 00:41:17,141
No!

557
00:41:17,141 --> 00:41:19,743
It's my first orchestra.

558
00:41:19,743 --> 00:41:21,589
Me?

559
00:41:21,589 --> 00:41:23,547
I can't quit.

560
00:41:23,547 --> 00:41:25,986
I won't quit!

561
00:41:25,986 --> 00:41:30,738
I'm the bandmaster.
It's my orchestra!

562
00:41:30,738 --> 00:41:32,923
I want to do well, too.

563
00:41:32,923 --> 00:41:38,629
I want to balance you
and the members...

564
00:41:38,629 --> 00:41:41,131
because that's the bandmaster's job.

565
00:41:41,131 --> 00:41:46,803
I really wanted to do well...

566
00:41:51,887 --> 00:41:53,957
"My orchestra"?

567
00:41:54,812 --> 00:41:56,968
You said...

568
00:41:56,968 --> 00:41:59,529
you'd give me until tomorrow.

569
00:42:00,354 --> 00:42:02,356
Until tomorrow...

570
00:42:02,356 --> 00:42:04,159
it's my orchestra.

571
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:07,859
Go wash your face.
Let's start your lesson.

572
00:42:07,859 --> 00:42:10,030
You improved a lot compared
to before.

573
00:42:10,030 --> 00:42:11,430
Really?

574
00:42:13,367 --> 00:42:16,561
But I can't do it tonight.
Let's do it tomorrow. Tomorrow!

575
00:42:16,561 --> 00:42:18,933
- Let's do it tomorrow.
- Orabang...

576
00:42:18,933 --> 00:42:21,667
Of course kimchi stew is the best.

577
00:42:21,667 --> 00:42:23,752
Spicy sausage stew is
the best for drinking.

578
00:42:23,752 --> 00:42:25,546
He wouldn't eat
that hodgepodge stew!

579
00:42:25,546 --> 00:42:27,278
I'm not eating!

580
00:42:27,278 --> 00:42:28,879
Just one bite.

581
00:42:28,879 --> 00:42:30,926
Just one bite, Orabang!

582
00:42:30,926 --> 00:42:32,357
Almighty Cha!

583
00:42:33,479 --> 00:42:34,985
Just a taste.

584
00:42:38,655 --> 00:42:41,184
What's with that shirt and
strange movement?

585
00:42:41,184 --> 00:42:43,814
Isn't it cool? I added
a performance element.

586
00:42:43,814 --> 00:42:46,471
The image of spirit
befitting the music!

587
00:42:47,398 --> 00:42:49,442
Doesn't it look like avant-garde art?

588
00:42:49,442 --> 00:42:53,279
Orabang, can you please try it on?

589
00:42:53,279 --> 00:42:57,244
Isn't it awesome? This is the special T-shirt!

590
00:42:57,244 --> 00:42:58,868
Image?

591
00:42:58,868 --> 00:43:02,163
Express it in the notes.
Don't do weird things.

592
00:43:02,163 --> 00:43:04,532
Yoo Jin, you're great in everything,
but you have no flexibility.

593
00:43:04,532 --> 00:43:05,917
You have to make some risks!

594
00:43:05,917 --> 00:43:08,352
This music also came to life
when Beethoven was adventurous.

595
00:43:08,352 --> 00:43:12,052
Carry on Beethoven's spirit with
a rock feeling orchestra!

596
00:43:12,052 --> 00:43:15,222
- Isn't it awesome?
- Yeah.

597
00:43:17,639 --> 00:43:19,349
The response is overwhelming.

598
00:43:19,349 --> 00:43:21,618
How many times have I said
that we have no time?

599
00:43:22,819 --> 00:43:24,915
Don't think about using a trick...

600
00:43:24,915 --> 00:43:27,604
Think about getting
recognized through music.

601
00:43:28,984 --> 00:43:31,812
Orabang, can you still
put it on just once?

602
00:43:31,812 --> 00:43:34,310
- I think you'll look good in it.
- That's right!

603
00:43:34,310 --> 00:43:37,294
- Just look...
- If you keep interrupting...

604
00:43:37,294 --> 00:43:39,996
I'll strip you of the bandmaster role.

605
00:43:42,319 --> 00:43:44,687
Of course practice
is the most important!

606
00:44:20,351 --> 00:44:24,552
Competitions may help
students grow but..

607
00:44:25,207 --> 00:44:27,476
It's painful to
watch them compete.

608
00:44:28,168 --> 00:44:31,135
There is no right answer, Mina.

609
00:44:31,135 --> 00:44:33,429
I know, but...

610
00:44:35,008 --> 00:44:37,510
Do you have a favor to ask?

611
00:44:44,059 --> 00:44:47,729
When you gave up the piano...

612
00:44:47,729 --> 00:44:52,089
I wasn't able to protect your music.

613
00:44:52,089 --> 00:44:54,791
Although I loved your music...

614
00:44:57,531 --> 00:45:00,567
more than anyone else.

615
00:45:01,782 --> 00:45:09,245
So if you need me,
just use me anytime.

616
00:45:17,050 --> 00:45:19,342
Excuse me, sir..

617
00:45:19,342 --> 00:45:23,371
What would you choose
between love and friendship?

618
00:45:23,371 --> 00:45:25,239
Of course it's love.

619
00:45:26,056 --> 00:45:27,349
Why?

620
00:45:27,349 --> 00:45:30,063
You have to love someone
to have a son.

621
00:45:30,063 --> 00:45:33,710
There is nothing more
important than a son.

622
00:45:34,231 --> 00:45:36,366
Do you like Lak that much?

623
00:45:36,366 --> 00:45:39,156
Every time you look at Lak,
your eyes shoot out hearts.

624
00:45:39,156 --> 00:45:41,425
Of course! He's my son.

625
00:45:42,119 --> 00:45:44,046
Hi Lak!

626
00:45:44,046 --> 00:45:45,572
Father, can I have juice?

627
00:45:45,572 --> 00:45:48,100
Why did you come down?
You should've called me!

628
00:45:48,100 --> 00:45:49,665
Just wait a sec.

629
00:45:53,810 --> 00:45:55,611
Hey, Seol Nae Il!

630
00:45:56,280 --> 00:45:58,502
Are you friends with Min Hee?

631
00:45:58,502 --> 00:46:00,236
Mini Min Hee?

632
00:46:00,844 --> 00:46:02,464
Why?

633
00:46:05,015 --> 00:46:06,983
I think I'm close..

634
00:46:10,466 --> 00:46:13,002
Orabang! You're going to look
for Mini Min Hee, right?

635
00:46:13,002 --> 00:46:15,838
There was a rumor that you
asked Lak about it...

636
00:46:16,573 --> 00:46:19,075
I'm going to check if she'll
continue on with the orchestra.

637
00:46:19,075 --> 00:46:21,144
I can't reach her.

638
00:46:21,144 --> 00:46:25,341
Orabang, you're embarrassed.

639
00:46:25,341 --> 00:46:28,785
Mini Min Hee couldn't pay her
cellphone bill, so it stopped.

640
00:46:28,785 --> 00:46:32,422
And she works part-time at a convenience
store on weekends, so follow me.

641
00:46:32,422 --> 00:46:34,591
I know how to get to the area.

642
00:46:34,591 --> 00:46:37,827
Isn't it better to work part-time
for weddings and such?

643
00:46:38,715 --> 00:46:41,497
Performance fees are cut
by middle men, it doesn't add up.

644
00:46:41,497 --> 00:46:44,533
And it's not consistent.

645
00:46:45,347 --> 00:46:47,503
Mini Min Hee!

646
00:46:47,503 --> 00:46:49,906
Hey, you said
it was that way earlier.

647
00:46:49,906 --> 00:46:52,675
Yes, it was that way.

648
00:46:53,394 --> 00:46:55,961
But there are too many
convenience stores around!

649
00:46:55,961 --> 00:46:57,829
Where is she!

650
00:46:59,820 --> 00:47:01,071
Mini Min Hee!

651
00:47:01,071 --> 00:47:04,387
I thought I only had to
take care of the counter.

652
00:47:04,387 --> 00:47:06,282
Working at a convenience
store is about doing chores!

653
00:47:06,282 --> 00:47:08,078
Are you some princess?

654
00:47:08,078 --> 00:47:10,593
- Why worry about Your wrists?
- Still...

655
00:47:10,593 --> 00:47:13,789
I sprained my wrist
carrying boxes yesterday...

656
00:47:13,789 --> 00:47:16,493
That's because you weren't careful!

657
00:47:16,493 --> 00:47:20,402
Just pay for the broken
bottles and leave. Get lost!

658
00:47:23,406 --> 00:47:25,108
Is that worth something?

659
00:47:25,108 --> 00:47:26,135
Let's make it even with that.

660
00:47:26,135 --> 00:47:29,145
No, you can't!
That's my contrabass.

661
00:47:29,145 --> 00:47:31,881
- What's wrong with her?
- Mister...

662
00:47:31,881 --> 00:47:33,687
- Let go of me!
- No...

663
00:47:33,687 --> 00:47:35,394
You little..

664
00:47:35,394 --> 00:47:38,655
You... You want to go to prison?

665
00:47:38,655 --> 00:47:41,323
You want me to involve the law?

666
00:47:41,904 --> 00:47:43,113
Are you okay, Mini Min Hee?

667
00:47:43,113 --> 00:47:45,073
Taking someone else's
instrument by force is a crime.

668
00:47:45,073 --> 00:47:47,117
Who the hell are you?

669
00:47:47,117 --> 00:47:49,666
- Did you receive minimum wage?
- What?

670
00:47:49,666 --> 00:47:52,253
Did you write down
your work hours?

671
00:47:52,956 --> 00:47:54,217
What about overtime?

672
00:47:54,217 --> 00:47:55,725
Overtime?

673
00:47:56,839 --> 00:48:00,610
Shall we take a look at how good
you were at sticking to the law?

674
00:48:00,610 --> 00:48:02,606
Yoo Jin...

675
00:48:21,527 --> 00:48:22,903
Mini Min Hee!

676
00:48:22,903 --> 00:48:25,397
- You're early today.
- Yes.

677
00:48:25,397 --> 00:48:28,155
I started teaching
a junior-high student,

678
00:48:28,155 --> 00:48:30,396
so I quit one part-time job.

679
00:48:31,119 --> 00:48:32,579
Really? That's great.

680
00:48:32,579 --> 00:48:35,527
I didn't think I'd ever get
a chance to land that kind of job,

681
00:48:35,527 --> 00:48:41,132
I don't know how they managed to contacted me.

682
00:48:46,966 --> 00:48:49,166
Mini Min Hee, give it your best today!

683
00:48:49,166 --> 00:48:50,193
Let's do it!

684
00:48:50,193 --> 00:48:52,027
Bye.

685
00:49:01,270 --> 00:49:02,898
What is it?

686
00:49:02,898 --> 00:49:08,198
Orabang, your brain is good,
but I think your heart is better.

687
00:49:08,198 --> 00:49:09,835
Shut up.

688
00:49:15,191 --> 00:49:16,892
Let's practice.

689
00:49:17,833 --> 00:49:19,713
You're so shy.

690
00:49:42,149 --> 00:49:44,217
Cha Yoo Jin!

691
00:49:45,060 --> 00:49:47,855
Guys! You can't run away!

692
00:49:47,855 --> 00:49:49,952
I can't do it anymore.

693
00:49:49,952 --> 00:49:52,088
He thinks he's an emperor!

694
00:49:52,088 --> 00:49:53,911
This is dictatorship!

695
00:49:53,911 --> 00:49:56,869
I don't have any confidence left.
Yoo Jin hates me!

696
00:49:56,869 --> 00:50:01,072
No, Almighty Cha is fair...
He hates all of us.

697
00:50:01,793 --> 00:50:04,786
And you've improved a lot recently.

698
00:50:06,795 --> 00:50:09,215
- Really?
- Yes!

699
00:50:09,215 --> 00:50:12,295
Yoo Jin is so annoying!

700
00:50:19,269 --> 00:50:21,769
Hey, are you crying?

701
00:50:21,769 --> 00:50:23,815
Yoo Jin, really...

702
00:50:23,815 --> 00:50:26,017
Don't cry!

703
00:50:35,164 --> 00:50:37,466
Six judges...

704
00:50:38,205 --> 00:50:40,937
It's one professor from each major.

705
00:50:40,937 --> 00:50:44,173
I happened to become
the judge from the piano major.

706
00:50:44,173 --> 00:50:47,878
Three judges will follow
the board's order.

707
00:50:47,878 --> 00:50:51,426
Do we have to hope for fairness
from the other three?

708
00:51:10,333 --> 00:51:14,488
They are not losers anymore.

709
00:51:14,488 --> 00:51:18,432
They're playing it right, following
my lead and the music.

710
00:51:35,554 --> 00:51:39,238
The sound is... subtly off.

711
00:51:40,830 --> 00:51:45,052
No one... is looking at the conductor.

712
00:52:00,444 --> 00:52:01,730
Sorry, Yoo Jin.

713
00:52:01,730 --> 00:52:04,086
We were looking at the score,
so we forgot to look at you.

714
00:52:04,086 --> 00:52:05,638
Me too.

715
00:52:06,258 --> 00:52:08,082
No, it's okay.

716
00:52:19,720 --> 00:52:25,851
Orabang... I thought you liked today's performance.

717
00:52:25,851 --> 00:52:29,399
Yes, but something's wrong.

718
00:52:30,609 --> 00:52:32,348
It was accurate.

719
00:52:32,348 --> 00:52:34,641
What was it?

720
00:52:38,888 --> 00:52:42,958
Orabang, just wait a sec.
I'll play the piano for you.

721
00:52:43,455 --> 00:52:45,824
I want to be alone,
so just go home.

722
00:52:56,593 --> 00:52:58,383
You remember that?

723
00:52:59,475 --> 00:53:02,778
Yes, because I heard it everyday.

724
00:53:03,312 --> 00:53:07,123
This music... is a bit complicated...

725
00:53:07,980 --> 00:53:10,152
but this is really fun music.

726
00:53:10,152 --> 00:53:12,154
Orabang, just listen to it.

727
00:53:12,154 --> 00:53:15,491
Then you'll find what the problem is.

728
00:53:22,164 --> 00:53:25,267
If you play it the way you want,
how can I find the problem?

729
00:53:37,259 --> 00:53:39,928
Playful, soaring...

730
00:53:45,154 --> 00:53:48,648
Interpretation with no calculation.

731
00:54:10,613 --> 00:54:15,884
Now I realize why Maestro
picked all of you.

732
00:54:37,006 --> 00:54:39,205
Orabang!

733
00:54:39,205 --> 00:54:41,240
Today is the day!

734
00:54:41,240 --> 00:54:43,742
You didn't leave without me, did you?

735
00:54:55,587 --> 00:55:00,091
Orabang, if you don't wake up now,
I'm going to get you.

736
00:55:08,204 --> 00:55:09,891
I'm coming!

737
00:55:26,428 --> 00:55:28,084
Oh my gosh!

738
00:55:31,060 --> 00:55:33,895
You didn't do anything to me
while I was asleep, did you?

739
00:55:35,063 --> 00:55:36,846
What time is it?

740
00:55:37,713 --> 00:55:39,576
Why didn't you wake me up?

741
00:55:57,441 --> 00:56:01,188
[Han Eum Orchestra Autumn Concert]

742
00:56:05,594 --> 00:56:08,657
I'm sure you know the decision
by the board of directors.

743
00:56:08,657 --> 00:56:12,119
I also know very well
that it's difficult

744
00:56:12,119 --> 00:56:15,713
to manage two
orchestras in reality.

745
00:56:15,713 --> 00:56:19,918
S Orchestra shouldn't have
been created to begin with.

746
00:56:19,918 --> 00:56:23,235
It's an obvious decision to disband
the one with a lower score.

747
00:56:24,756 --> 00:56:27,513
I ask you for your fair judgment

748
00:56:28,350 --> 00:56:30,679
so that students can accept the result.

749
00:56:30,679 --> 00:56:34,394
For the sake of fair judgment,

750
00:56:34,394 --> 00:56:37,214
shouldn't the professors
in charge withdraw from voting?

751
00:56:38,482 --> 00:56:41,777
Please exclude Professor Ahn
Ahn Geon Sung from judging.

752
00:56:41,777 --> 00:56:44,584
He can't lead one orchestra and just both.

753
00:56:46,073 --> 00:56:48,609
People will be suspicious.

754
00:56:50,118 --> 00:56:53,455
It'll be fair if I join in.

755
00:57:25,150 --> 00:57:27,243
Orabang!

756
00:57:27,243 --> 00:57:29,345
- Wait a minute.
- What?

757
00:57:29,345 --> 00:57:32,147
You didn't get any sleep last night.

758
00:57:32,147 --> 00:57:34,246
Take this and gather
up your energy.

759
00:57:34,246 --> 00:57:37,182
You'll do a better job
of conducting, too.

760
00:57:59,108 --> 00:58:00,647
Focus.

761
00:58:03,609 --> 00:58:06,525
So this is how good A Orchestra is.

762
00:58:06,525 --> 00:58:07,984
You didn't expect this?

763
00:58:07,984 --> 00:58:10,278
I didn't know
they were this good.

764
00:58:10,278 --> 00:58:13,198
Do you think we can win?

765
00:58:13,198 --> 00:58:16,413
If we lose, our orchestra
will be disbanded.

766
00:58:17,026 --> 00:58:20,729
We're good, too!
We can win!

767
00:58:45,788 --> 00:58:47,784
Tear up your music sheets.
